This paper deals with sentiment analysis and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer science. Specifically, it focuses on the interpretation of subjective language, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a rule-based framework for analyzing opinion implicatures, which involves making inferences based on implicit information in the text. This type of reasoning is often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and interpreting textual data, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.NE).
